<HEADLINE> Top Union Leader Watches Drama On Laid-Off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, chairman of the
All-China Federation of Trade Unions, today joined an audience of
800 here to watch a drama about the life of a family whose members
all work for state-owned factories.
</P>
<P>
Wei is a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The drama, which was jointly written and performed by the
Qingdao City Trade Union Bureau and the Qingdao Drama Theater,
tells of how the family members try to tackle their problems and
difficulties when their factories undergo temporary troubles.
</P>
<P>
The drama has already been performed 36 times in Qingdao City,
in east China's Shandong Province, where more than 20,000 people
saw it.
</P>
<P>
The drama will continue to be performed in the Chinese capital
until May 10, at the invitation of the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions and the Ministry of Culture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
