<HEADLINE> China's Chief Legislator Grieves for Linh Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, Chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC), China's highest legislature, sent a
message of condolence on Tuesday to Vietnam's National Assembly
Chairman Nong Duc Manh on the death of Nguyen Van Linh, former
general secretary of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
"I am distressed to learn of Linh's passing," Li said. "On
behalf of the NPC Standing Committee, please accept my profound
condolences, and convey my solicitude to his family.
</P>
<P>
"Linh was a veteran revolutionary in Vietnam and an old friend
of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
"During his tenure of office, he made major contributions to
the cause of Vietnamese socialist construction and renovation, to
the normalization and the development of bilateral relations
between the two countries and the two parties," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Linh died on Monday at the age of 82 in southern Ho Chi Minh
City.
</P>
<P>
He was elected the general secretary of the Central Committee
of the CPV in 1986. 
</P>
