<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Will Revive Vigor, Tung Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The worst effects of the
financial turmoil are now over and after a period of adjustment,
Hong Kong will surely regain all its vigor, Chief Executive of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa said
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing SAR deputies to the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), Tung said that since the latter
half of 1997, Hong Kong economy and Hong Kong people have been
suffering from the regional financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Therefore topping the agenda of the SAR government is to take
all necessary measures, such as slashing taxes and increasing
public investment, to get Hong Kong economy out of the straits as
soon as possible and at the same time to alleviate the pains felt
by Hong Kong people and recover their confidence in the city, the
SAR leader said.
</P>
<P>
Tung noted that Hong Kong's current situation ranks best among
Southeast Asian countries and regions. With the approaching of a
new round of economic growth on the Chinese mainland, the
economic hinterland of Hong Kong, and strong support from the
Central People's Government, he added, "we have every reason to be
fully confident of Hong Kong's future."
</P>
<P>
Finally, he called upon the CPPCC deputies to make joint
efforts with the SAR government and people from all walks of life
in Hong Kong to tide over the current difficulties and create a
better future for Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
