<HEADLINE> HK Federation of Trade Unions Marks Birthday, May Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Federation of
Trade Unions (HKFTU) gave a reception here Tuesday to celebrate
its 50th birthday and the upcoming May Day.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Chief Executive
Tung Chee Hwa was present at the reception.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Lee Chark Tin, president of the
HKFTU, said that after 50 years of development, there are now 134
trade unions with some 270,000 members in the HKFTU.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of the federation in April 1948, the HKFTU
has been upholding its patriotic position and sticking to its aim
of serving the workers, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
The federation has won the trust and support of grassroots
masses and the recognition and acceptance of various classes in
Hong Kong, Lee noted.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return to China on July 1, 1997, the overall
situation in Hong Kong is very good and Hong Kong remains
prosperous and stable as the policies of "one country, two
systems," "Hong Kong People governing Hong Kong" and a high degree
 of autonomy have been successfully implemented, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
He said the recent Asian financial turmoil has affected the
workers' lives. But with the effort of the Hong Kong people, under
the leadership of the SAR government and with support from the
state, the temporary difficulties will surely be overcome, Lee
stressed.
</P>
<P>
At the reception, Chief Executive Tung expressed his respect to
 the labor sector, which he said has contributed a lot to the
current achievements of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Tung said the SAR government is concerned over the loss and
pain caused to citizens by the recent Asian financial turmoil. He
stressed that the government will try its best to overcome the
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Tung noted that the fundamentals of Hong Kong are good and with
the support of the state, the economy of Hong Kong will recover
soon and Hong Kong's future will be better.
</P>
<P>
Among the about 1,000 guests at the reception were SAR
government officials, delegates of the All China Federation of
Trade Unions and the Federation of Trade Unions of Guangdong
Province and representatives of trade unions from Macao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
