<HEADLINE> Pakistani PM Meets Saudi Prince </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif met here Tuesday with visiting Saudi Arabian Prince Salman
Bin Abdul Aziz and had friendly talks with him.
</P>
<P>
According to the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP), Sharif and
the Saudi prince discussed bilateral matters as well as issues of
common concern including Palestine, Kashmir and Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting was held in an atmosphere of great warmth and
cordiality, reflecting the close and fraternal ties between the
peoples of Pakistan and Saudi Arabia," the APP said.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi prince described the relations between Saudi Arabia
and Pakistan as deep-rooted and expressed satisfaction that the
two countries held bilateral consultations on international issues
on a regular basis.
</P>
<P>
The prince voiced Saudi Arabia's concern over the continued
denial of the right of self-determination to the people of Kashmir
and reiterated his country's support for Pakistan's principled
position on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said strengthening Pakistan's relations with Saudi
Arabia is part of his government's agenda and he would continue
making efforts for further consolidation of these valuable ties.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi prince, who is heading a 41-member delegation,
arrived here Monday on a five-day visit at the invitation of
Sharif. 
</P>
</TEXT>
