<HEADLINE> France to Mark Russian Film Maker's Centenary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- France will mark the centenary of
the birth of Russian legendary film-maker Sergei Eisenstein by
putting on a series of his films in Paris, Lyon and Marseille from
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the films to be seen by film fans will be Eisenstein's
milestone "Battleship Potemkin," "Strike," "Alexander Nevski" and
"Ivan the Terrible."
</P>
<P>
The program was initiated by the Films Without Frontiers
company headed by Galeshka Moravioff.
</P>
<P>
Eisenstein was born on January 23, 1898 in Riga, Lithuania, and
died of a heart attack at the age of 50 in Moscow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
