<HEADLINE> Chinese President Mourns Death of Nguyen Van Linh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, General Secretary of
the Communist Party and President of China, sent a message of
condolence Tuesday to Le Kha Phieu, General Secretary of the
Vietnamese Communist Party, on the death of Nguyen Van Linh.
</P>
<P>
"It is a shock to hear of the death of Comrade Nguyen Van
Linh," Jiang said in the message. "I feel deeply grieved," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Linh, a former general secretary of the Vietnamese Communist
Party (CPV), died on Monday at the age of 82.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that Linh was a veteran revolutionary in Vietnam and
an old friend of China.
</P>
<P>
"He devoted his whole life to the cause of renovation and
socialist construction in Vietnam," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Linh also made great contributions to restoring and developing
party ties and bilateral relations between China and Vietnam,
Jiang said, adding that his death is a great loss to the CPV and
the Vietnamese people.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the Chinese Communist Party, government and
people, I express my heartfelt condolences to you," the Chinese
president said. He also asked Le Kha Phieu to convey his
condolences to Nguyen's family members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
