<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A Thai senator called here Tuesday
for global financial reform, saying the current Asian financial
crisis is not just a crisis in Asia and international cooperation
is needed.
</P>
<P>
"Global finance as being practised today is in need of reform,"
said Narongchai Akrasanee at a seminar on the Asian financial
crisis held before the Asian Development Bank (ADB) begins its
annual meeting here in Geneva from April 29 to May 1.
</P>
<P>
After recalling what had happened to Thailand following the
financial crisis, which started in Thailand last July and spread
to many parts of Asia, Akrasanee stressed that experiences with
the financial crisis in Thailand should be taken as a lesson in
economic development and in reviewing global financial order.
</P>
<P>
"This task will have to be performed by major industrialized
countries and the relevant international organizations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is obvious that a developing country cannot introduce
financial sector reform by itself," Akrasanee said. "International
cooperation is needed." 
