<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-28 16:53 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Liberalizes Foreign Currency Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Israel unveiled a foreign
currency liberalization program on Tuesday, lifting most of the
restrictions on currency exchange in the country.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, Finance Minister
Yaakov Neeman and Governor of Bank of Israel Jacob Frenkel
announced the program at a joint news conference held here.
</P>
<P>
This marked the completion of the process of removing
foreign-currency restrictions on Israeli residents - individuals
and businesses - which started at the end of the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The program allows Israeli residents complete freedom to engage
in transactions of both foreign and local currencies, and to invest
abroad, including in land and real estate. So far such investments
were controlled by the government.
</P>
<P>
The program also abolishes the restriction on holding foreign
currency in cash; payments in foreign currency will be permitted
in cash or by check.
</P>
<P>
But there does remain a short list of restrictions, such as on
direct investments abroad by pension funds, provident funds and
insurance companies, which are expected to be removed in the next
stage of the liberalization process.
</P>
<P>
This is because of the apprehension that foreign investors
would practice financial manipulation which would shake Israel's
economy.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu told the news conference that the program will
simplify transactions and expand opportunities for Israeli
residents in the management of their assets and liabilities
portfolios.
</P>
<P>
Neeman said the program is one of the key steps in Israel's
integration into the global economy.
</P>
<P>
He said that it will thus encourage foreign investment in
Israel's economy, help to boost growth and create employment, and
open new channels for investment abroad and for domestic savings.
</P>
<P>
The liberalization measures will take effect after the Israeli
Knesset (parliament) approves them in a few days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0025 </DOCNO>
