progress made in the verification and Iraq failed to provide the
UNSCOM with new documents about its weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
The UNSCOM had achieved some progress in its inspection work in
the recent weeks because of the cooperation given by Iraq, and the
inspection could be finished quickly if Iraq provided the UNSCOM
with all the documents it wanted to verify, he said. 
