<HEADLINE> 6 More Killed as Somali Clan War Goes on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The fighting in Southern
Somalia continues for the fifth day Tuesday with the militiamen
from the Majerten sub-clan making further advances to the North
or the territories controlled by factional leader Hussein Aidid.
</P>
<P>
Heavy artillery and mortar exchange fire continued from Monday
night until Tuesday morning at Kansuma, 120 km North of Kismayu,
before the village has fallen to the militiamen of General
Mohamed Said Hirsi Morgan late Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The fighting has then spread to the district of Jamama, nearly
100 km Northeast of Kismayu Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to one of the VHF radio operators in Jamama district
who escaped the fighting with his radio apparatus to the nearby
jungle, the anti-aircraft machine-guns mounted on the battle
wagons have reached the town at 15:00 hours local time Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Some reports say that the town has already fallen to the
forces of General Morgan. The radio operators revealed that six
people were killed and 12 others suffered gunshot wounds during
the battle.
</P>
<P>
However, the casualties on General Morgan's side is not yet
confirmed, but reports from the Southern port town of Kismayu,
500 km South of Mogadishu, said four of their militiamen have
died in Monday night's operation and several others were wounded.
</P>
<P>
Observers here in Mogadishu express concern that this renewed
hostility among the Darod sub-clans and now spreading to the
Hawiye-dominated territories may escalate to a more catastrophic
fighting similar to that in 1991 which took place between the
Hawiye and Darod communities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
