<HEADLINE> Greece's Airport to Be Closed for Runway Maintenance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Thessaloniki
international airport, the biggest one in northern Greece, will be
closed on May 8-12 for runway maintenance.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day closure, most domestic and international
airlines will be diverted to the Kavala airport, about 150
kilometers northeast of Thessaloniki, the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA) reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
One runway is already out of action for replacement of its
asphalt surface.
</P>
