<HEADLINE> Zelezny s Career Threatened by His Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Javelin world record holde1r Jan
Zelezny's career is threatened by injury and surgery, doctors said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Zelezny hurt himself in training on Thursday and had surgery in
Prague on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"He is out of all events this year, for sure," chief surgeon
Vaclav Smetana was quoted as saying. "His whole career is in
doubt".
</P>
<P>
Zelezny was hit in the ankle by a weight he pulled on a rubber
band, fell on the ground and hit his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
Doctors found torn ligaments and a dismembered
acromioclavicular joint, essential for all javelin throwers. The
joint connects the scapula bone in the back to the clavicula, the
long bone between the chest and the shoulder, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old, 31, won Olympic gold in Barcelona and Atlanta,
and holds the world record at 98.48 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
