<HEADLINE> Macao Government to Support SAR Preparatory Committee: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira
said on Wednesday that the Macao Government will fully support the
work of the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) Preparatory
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The namelist of the Macao SAR Preparatory Committee was adopted
by China's National People's Congress on Wednesday afternoon. To
be formally established in May, the committee has 60 members from
Macao and the remaining 40 from China's inland.
</P>
<P>
The governor said his government's support for the Preparatory
Committee aims to ensure that the future Macao SAR Government can
be established on a solid basis, according to a press release
issued by the Government Information Office on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The governor stressed that his government will work with the
committee "effectively and seriously" and handle affairs related
to Macao on the basis of respecting each other's rights and power.
</P>
<P>
The leading members of the committee all have profound
knowledge of Macao and are capable of working in favor of Macao
and protecting the interests of Macao, he commented.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the governor has appointed Jorge Rangel, secretary
for administration, education and youth affairs, as the liaison
person between his government and the Preparatory Committee
because, he said, the secretary takes charge of administration
affairs and knows Chinese language. 
</P>
