</P>
<P>
A total trade volume of 40 million shares traded Wednesday
against 36 million shares traded the previous day.
</P>
<P>
There were 62 gainers, 82 losers while share prices of 59
companies remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The KSE-100 Index closed lower Wednesday as the cement sector
came under pressure after a government announcement that a cartel
like situation had been developed in the cement industry.
</P>
<P>
Cement stocks came under heavy selling Wednesday morning and
led the bourse into a selling spree. The earlier announcement by
the government about the cement industry has led to an artificial
shortage of cement and rising prices.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday's session was marked by disinterest from foreign and
institutional buyers. Brokers expect that this trend is to
continue for some days. 
