<HEADLINE> China Makes Progress in "Green Car" Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China has kept pace with the
development of green car technologies worldwide by making major
progress in producing environmentally friendly automobiles.
</P>
<P>
An official from the State Bureau of the Machinery Industry
told Xinhua that China has concentrated on several key programs in
this respect.
</P>
<P>
They include updating the widely-used Model 492 engine,
spreading the use of electronic fuel ejection and ignition systems
in automobiles, and developing and commercializing catalytic
converters for reducing harmful gas emission.
</P>
<P>
China has joined hands with the Ford Company of the United
States to develop rare earth catalytic converters. The jointly
developed product will be put onto market in two years' time. Tests
in the US have proved that the product can reduce harmful gas
emission by 70 to 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China has already developed cars that use
alternative fuels such as natural gas, methanol, ethanol,
electricity and solar energy.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts believe that natural gas-fueled cars and
ones using combined fuels are the best choice for the China market
in terms of investment and resources.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Pan Asia-Pacific Scientific and Technological
Development Company and two companies in Shanghai have jointly
made breakthroughs in key technologies for producing multi-fuel
automobiles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
