<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 14:25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian MP Ready to Get Kuwaiti POWs in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A visiting Iranian member of
parliament expressed willingness on Wednesday to mediate the
release of Kuwait's prisoners of war held in Iraq if she is asked,
the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Kuwait Red Crescent Society, Zahra Pishgahifard
said that "to mediate in the release of POWs is a legislative and
religious duty. If you want us to mediate ... in this Islamic,
humanitarian issue, then we are ready to do so."
</P>
<P>
Pishgahifard is one of the delegates accompanying Iranian
Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri on a three-day official
visit to Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
"From an Islamic and humanitarian point of view, we wish that
all the POWs in Iraqi prisons, whether Iranians or Kuwaitis, are
promptly released," Pishgahifard said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait insists that there are still 625 people, 550 of them
kuwaitis, missing becuase of Iraq's seven-month occupation of
Kuwait from August, 1990. But Iraq has denied that it has any
Kuwaiti POWs.
</P>
<P>
The issue of POWs remains the most thorny problem in the ties
bewtween Kuwait and Iraq after Iraq recognized the common border
and started to pay compensations under the supervision of the
United Nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
