<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-Uzbekistan Judicial Assistance Accord Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- An accord on civilian and
criminal judicial assistance between China and Uzbekistan was
approved here today at the second meeting of the Standing
Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by the State Council, Vice-Foreign Minister Zhang
Deguang made an explanation of the accord that was submitted to
the NPC Standing Committee meeting April 26.
</P>
<P>
He said relations between China and Uzbekistan have been
progressing rapidly since the two countries established diplomatic
ties, noting that it is necessary for the two countries to conduct
judicial assistance with each other to protect the legitimate rights
and interests of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
In April 1996 Uzbekistan set forth a suggestion to China on
negotiating accords on civilian and criminal judicial assistance
and extradition.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen, who was also foreign minister
then, and visiting Uzbekistan Foreign Minister Kamilov Abdulaziz
Hafizovich signed an accord on bilateral judicial assistance last
December.
</P>
<P>
The accord contains 34 articles, and its main contents include
offering judicial protection to nationals of the other country,
recognition and implementation of civilian adjudication, and
exchange of legal information.
</P>
<P>
Zhang noted that the bilateral judicial assistance accord
complies with the basic principles of the related Chinese laws and
judicial practice as well as international laws.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, it does not exceed the scope of the judicial
assistance accords China has signed with other nations of the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), while taking into
account the judicial system and practices of Uzbekistan, he added.
</P>
<P>
He also pointed out that the accord will help to increase
judicial cooperation between China and Uzbekistan, and boost
bilateral mutual economic, trade and personnel exchanges.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0106 </DOCNO>
