<HEADLINE> Heavy Rain Relieves Drought-Hit Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest
China has received some relief from a long and severe drought as
its western part has experienced heavy rainfall ranging from 50
mm-100 mm in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
But the drought in the eastern part of the province is yet to
be eased, according to local weathermen.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has witnessed its most serious drought since 1949
recently, with 116 counties affected. Nearly half of the province
has seen a 80-90 percent decrease in rainfall compared with normal
years.
</P>
<P>
According to local disaster-relief departments, five million
people, 4.4 million head of livestock and 1.39 million ha of
farmland has been affected.  
</P>
