<HEADLINE> Development Zones Vital to Central China Province's Opening-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The development zones in central
China's Hubei Province, which were set up in the mid-1980s, have
come to act as important "windows" backing the province's opening
up.
</P>
<P>
Hubei's development zones, including three state-level and 24
provincial-level, had used foreign fund of 2.13 billion
U.S. dollars by the end of 1997, making up one-third of the total
of the province, according to Yin Guangzhi, director of the
office of the development zones.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,026 joint-ventures have been built up in the development
zones, accounting for one-seventh of those of the province, said
Yin.
</P>
<P>
They have so far put 13.4 billion yuan into infrastructure
construction and improved their working efficiency as well, Yin
added.
</P>
<P>
The development zones -- with the auto sector as its pillar
industry involving the major cities of Wuhan, Shiyan and Xiangfan
-- had generated Gross Domestic Product of 63.4 billion yuan by
the end of last year. 
</P>
