<HEADLINE> Li Peng Urges NPC Standing Committee to Enhance Supervisory Role (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li said that the NPC Standing Committee's supervisory role over
the State Council, the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme
People's Procuratorate is totally different from the restraining
role of the parliaments of some other countries over government
and judicial departments.
</P>
<P>
Thus, he said, in the NPC's work, supervision is expected to be
combined with support. While the NPC is performing its supervisory
function, it should also stress the role of support, and through
the supervision, the NPC expects the work of the government,
courts and procuratorates to be enhanced, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the relations between the law and the leadership of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), Li Peng said that the CPC is the
leading core of China's socialist construction and the CPC's
leading position has been formed by history.
</P>
<P>
He said that practice has proved that China cannot do without
the leading role of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
But, he said, the CPC should act in line with the Constitution
and laws.
</P>
<P>
He said that China's laws are formulated by the legislature
under the leadership of the CPC which has grasped the objective
rules of social development, summarized practical experiences and
concentrated the people's will.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it is a consistent view of the CPC that no people
or organizations have the power to act beyond the Constitution and
laws.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that the NPC Standing Committee is at the
forefront of the construction of the socialist legal system, and
it shares an important responsibility for the rule of law and
socialist legal construction in China.
</P>
<P>
He called on the members of the NPC Standing Committee to live
up to the expectations of the people of all nationalities, and to
do their work well with the utmost enthusiasm and a strong sense
of responsibility. 
</P>
</TEXT>
