<HEADLINE> Li Peng Urges NPC Standing Committee to Enhance Supervisory Role (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), today called on
the committee to enhance its supervisory role.
</P>
<P>
In his closing speech at the second meeting of the Ninth NPC
Standing Committee, Li urged China's highest legislative body to
improve its supervisory mechanism and raise the efficiency of its
supervision.
</P>
<P>
He said that examination of draft laws constitutes one of the
major ways that the NPC performs its supervisory function.
</P>
<P>
Such examinations should be part of the committee's regular
work, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on the members of the committee to be on guard
against formalism and to go to grass-root units to listen to the
people's opinions on legislation.
</P>
<P>
He said that some of the results of the examinations should be
made known to the public so that legislation becomes subject to
the supervision of both the NPC deputies and the people.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that the NPC Standing Committee should focus its
supervisory functions on the major issues of the country's reforms
and construction, as well as on other issues of great concern to
the people.
</P>
<P>
In the next few years the NPC Standing Committee is expected to
conduct supervision on some special topics so as to raise
all-round efficiency, he said.
</P>
<P>
The supervision will focus on some major issues on the basis of
examination of the working reports of the State Council, the
Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's Procuratorate, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the supervision work of the NPC is to promote and
support the roles of the government, the Supreme People's Court
and the Supreme People's Procuratorate in line with the laws, he
said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the NPC Standing Committee, the State Council,
the Supreme People's Court and the Supreme People's Procuratorate
are all state organs under the leadership of the Chinese Communist
Party, adding that although they have different functions, they
share identical objectives and basic starting points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
