<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Steffi Graf's Father Free From Jail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Peter Graf, father of the word
tennis star Steffi Graf, was released from jail Wednesday after
serving 10 months of a 45-month sentence for tax evasion, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
The 59-year-old Peter Graf was placed on parole for the rest of
his sentence, reports quoted the Stuttgart court as saying.
</P>
<P>
Graf was found guilty in January last year of cheating tax
authorities of 12 million marks (7.5 million U.S. dollars) by
hiding 42 million marks in revenue his daughter earned between
1989 and 1993.
</P>
<P>
Although he had only served 10 months of his prison term after
being jailed in July, he had already served 15 months on remand
prior to his imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
German law stipulates that a prisoner may be released on parole
once half the sentence has been served.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a court in the southern town of Ulm, where
Graf was imprisoned, turned down his application for parole.
</P>
<P>
Since December, Graf had been allowed out of prison during the
day but was obliged to return to his cell at night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
