<HEADLINE> Filipino Luzon Wins 12th Leg of Tour of the Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Bernard Luzon of the Philippines
took the 12th leg of the Tour of the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Luzon became the fifth rider to be a multi-stage winner by
finishing the 194.90-kilometer race in 5 hours, 19 minutes, 4
seconds, 45 seconds faster than compatriot Arnel Quirimit.
</P>
<P>
Quirimit, who came into the stage just 9 seconds behind
previous overall leader Warren Davadilla, finally overcame
Davidilla, also from the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Quirimit now became the overall leader of the race and led by 3
minutes, 39 seconds going into the last four stages of the race.
</P>
<P>
All 67 riders remaining from the starting roster of 84 were
able to finish Wednesday's leg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
