<HEADLINE> Top-seeded Rusedski Beaten at Munich Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Top seeded Greg Rusedski of Britain
was beaten by Oliver Gross of Germany 4-6, 0-6 in the first round
of the BMW Open tennis tournament in Munich, Germany, on Wednesday
</P>
<P>
Gross, 24, ranked No. 121 in the world but completely dominated
the Briton which is No. 5 in the world.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski couldn't draw power from his famous service on a cool
and damp day on the slow red clay.
</P>
<P>
Gross, whose career has been plagued by injuries, beat Pete
Sampras in 1995 in Barcelona for his only previous victory over a
Top 10 player. 
</P>
