<HEADLINE> Regional Orthopedics Meeting Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A three-day Inaugural Meeting
of Orthopedic Surgeons from SAARC countries opened here Wednesday
at the Birendra International Convention Center.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the meeting are some 350 doctors from Nepal,
India, Pakistan and Bangladesh. Bhutan, the Maldives and Sri
Lanka, the other three member countries of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC), have no delegates at
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
According to the agenda, the meeting organized by the Nepal
Orthopedic Association will hold sessions on a number of subjects
including innovative techniques, ortho-oncology, infection, tibia,
hip/acetabulum fractures, general orthopedics, adult
reconstruction (knee), arthroscopy, rehabilitation, trauma, spine
and adult reconstruction (hip).
</P>
<P>
Nepali Prime Minister Girija Prasad Koirala inaugurated the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Nepal Orthopedic Association said on the
occasion that 12 percent of the Nepalese are disabled, but the
country has only 40 orthopedic surgeons.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an exhibition on orthopedic instruments and medicine
opened at the Birendra International Convention Center. 
</P>
