<HEADLINE> Five New Mongolian Ministers appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's Parliament, the
Great Hural, appointed five government ministers on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the appointees were R. Amarjargal, who became the
Minister of External Relations; B. Batbayar the Minister of
Finance; S. Bayartsogt the Minister of Nature and Environment;
S. Batchuluun the Minister of Justice, and N. Altanhuyag the
Minister of Agriculture, Livestock Breeding and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian Prime Minister Tsakhiya Elbegdor on Monday mapped out
his nominees for the new cabinet, which is made up of 11 members,
and sent them to the Great Hural, which has the final
approval on the formation of a government.
</P>
<P>
The five nominations for ministers were adopted, while another
four failed to gain enough backing for approval. The appointment
for deputy prime ministry will be worked out after the Great
Hural's revision of the governmental law.
</P>
<P>
The new Mongolian government came into being in the wake of the
resignation of the former government headed by Mendsaikhan
Enkhsaikhan earlier this month. 
</P>
