<HEADLINE> EU Adopts Social Action Plan for 1998-2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission, the
executive body of the 15-nation European Union, adopted a new
social action program Wednesday for the years 1998-2000.
</P>
<P>
The commission has set a framework for the future development
of European social policy for that period.
</P>
<P>
The program, according to commission officials, focuses on
three priorities relevant to employment: skills and mobility, the
changing world of work, and the development of an inclusive
society.
</P>
<P>
The new program is built on the achievements of the previous
social action program for the years 1995-1997. It seeks to seize
upon the fresh impetus in the social field provided by the new
European employment strategy and the Treaty of Amsterdam.
</P>
<P>
The social program is expected to promote a decent quality of
life and standard of living for all in an active, inclusive and
healthy society, by emphasizing access to employment, good working
conditions and equal opportunity. 
</P>
