<HEADLINE> Remote Diagnosis Center Opens in Guiyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The China Jinwei Guiyang Remote
Diagnosis Center, the first of its kind in southwest China,
recently opened in Guiyang, capital of Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The project was jointly established by the Medical Management
Institute under the Ministry of Health and the Jinwei Medical
Networking Engineering Company.
</P>
<P>
The center features advanced computer and telecommunications
medical eqauipment, according to Liu Keqiang, director of the
center. The center's doctors consult with patients in person and
have ready access to remote transmissions of data, written and
audio materials and graphics, according to Liu.
</P>
<P>
Southwest China, a region densely populated with minority
groups, is not only economically underdeveloped, but also lacks
sound medical conditions.
</P>
<P>
China has opened over 20 similar diagnosis centers across the
country. 
</P>
