Tieling-Siping section of the Shenyang-Siping Expressway started
last October.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang-Shanhaiguan Expressway will be completed at an
estimated cost of 11 billion yuan (1.33 billion U.S. dollars),
including a 70 million U.S. dollar loans from the Asian
Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
China's operational expressway mileage currently stands at
4,735 km., including 597 km. in Liaoning. 
