<HEADLINE> Macao to Establish New Foundation to Promote Arts, Welfare </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Macao government is to
establish a new foundation soon to promote academic events,
culture, science, education, social and welfare affairs.
</P>
<P>
The governor has invited seven people, including Edmundo Ho
Hau Wah, president of the Macao Bankers' Association, Stanley Ho,
managing director of the Macao Tourism and Amusement Company
(STDM), as members of the trust committee of the Macao Development
and Cooperation Foundation.
</P>
<P>
