<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commercial Banks Urged to Increase Number of Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBOC)
today issued a circular urging all commercial banks to support
residential housing construction and consumption by further
increasing loans in this sector.
</P>
<P>
The circular pointed out that residential housing is a new leg
of growth for the national economy. It plays an important role in
restructuring the economy, increasing social demand, solving
residents' housing difficulties and reaching the economic growth
target.
</P>
<P>
All commercial banks should readjust their credit structure and
give more support to the residential housing industry, the
circular stated.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC demanded in the circular that, this year, 15 percent
of the newly increased loans should be channeled into residential
housing.
</P>
<P>
According to the circular, banks with the right to handle
housing loans have been extended from the original Industrial and
Commercial Bank, the Agricultural Bank and the Construction Bank
to all state-owned commercial banks and the Bank of Communications.
</P>
<P>
The circular also urged commercial banks to actively support
residential housing consumption by increasing home mortgages.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC stressed that the management of residential housing
credit business will be further standardized, and the PBOC will
gradually improve related management measures.
</P>
<P>
The commercial banks and branches of the PBOC are urged to step
up supervision and management of residential housing credit
business, to ensure that the credits are used for common
residential housing construction and consumption. No credit should
be used in developing high-grade commercial housing, the PBOC
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
