<HEADLINE> NPC Standing Committee Meeting Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Second Session of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC)
today approved three laws and decisions and some name lists.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, presided over
the closing meeting and delivered a speech.
</P>
<P>
One of the most important achievements of the session was the
approval of the 100-member name list of the Preparatory Committee
of the Macao Special Administrative Region, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Macao's smooth return to China in December 1999 will be the
second great event for the Chinese people since the return of Hong
Kong last year, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the preparatory committee signals an
important step forward in the process of the transition, as it has
a great role to play in this regard, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The session also approved the decision to amend the existing
Forestry Law. The amendments to the law will protect the nation's
forests and ensure the effective management of forestry resources,
Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Law on Fire Control was the only law passed at this
session. The law clarifies the responsibilities of the various
governmental levels and fire-control authorities, Li explained.
</P>
<P>
The law is needed to strictly safeguard public property, public
order and people's lives, Li added.
</P>
<P>
After four days of heated discussion and deliberation in
separate groups, the top legislature also approved the legal
assistance treaty between China and Uzbekistan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, name lists of senior officials of the Supreme
People's Procuratorate and local procuratorates were passed at
today's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
