<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Merger to Promote Automotive Air Conditioner Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China expects a Tuesday merger
between the largest domestic automotive air conditioning system
manufacturer and a Shanghai-based joint venture to significantly
improve related production levels.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-US venture--Shanghai Delphi Automotive Air
Conditioning Systems Co. Ltd,--involves a three-phase investment
of 88 million U.S. dollars, with the Chinese partner holding a 66
percent equity share.
</P>
<P>
The new joint venture, based in Shanghai's Pudong New Area,
will become the major supplier of automotive air conditioning
systems for domestically manufactured Santana and Buick model
vehicles. The venture also plans to target overseas markets. The
initial annual production capacity has been set at 700,000 units.
</P>
<P>
The former Shanghai Automotive Air Conditioning Systems Plant
was previously the largest domestic manufacturer of automotive
air conditioning systems with 70 percent in market share.
</P>
<P>
U.S.-based Delphi Co.. the world's leading automotive parts and
component supplier, has established 208 manufacturing plants in 36
countries. Delphi has invested some 350 million US dollars in 15
joint ventures in China since 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
