<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Supply for Newsprint Exceeds Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- China's newsprint market is
oversupplied, with supplies standing at 1.59 million tons and 1998
demand approaching one million tons this year, according to a
recent issue of Market Daily.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper reported that the newsprint market remains
competitive, with fierce competition expected for art paper as
related producers join the market and the ineffectiveness of
efforts to stem smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The article alluded to the possibility of downward trend in
prices of newsprint, especially in terms of this year's prices for
art paper. The trend remains a distinct possibility despite the
robust growth in the demand for newsprint used by news
organizations and publishers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
