<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bodhisattva Statue Inaugurated by Buddhists on Mount Wutai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- An inauguration ceremony for the
Bodhisattva statue and 500 Buddhist Arhats was held today on Mount
Wutai, a sacred Buddhist mountain in northern Shanxi Province, to
mark the birthday of the Bodhisattva.
</P>
<P>
Buddhists from all over the country, including Hong Kong and
Taiwan as well as Thailand, attended today's ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The statue of the Bodhisattva, personifying supreme wisdom and
patron deity of Mount Wutai, is housed in the Shuxiang Monastery
built in the Eastern Jin Dynasty (317-420). Sculptures of the 500
Buddhist Arhats, representing close disciples of the Buddha, are
also enshrined there.
</P>
<P>
To restore its former splendor, Monk Shengzhong, abbot of the
Shuxiang Monastery, raised money and spent one year to rebuild the
sculpture of the 500 Buddhist Arhats and coat gold foil on the
9.87-meter-tall Bodhisattva statue, which is regarded as the
largest and best molded statue of its kind in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
