<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Destroys Pirated VCDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Customs has destroyed
more than 4,300 pirated VCDs in a major action to combat smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The event marked the first time the local customs department has
destroyed pirated VCDs in public.
</P>
<P>
Jin Yugen, deputy director of Shanghai Customs, said that
battle against pirated VCDs has led to a ten-fold increase in
legally imported VCDs over 1996. More than two million VCDs were
imported through customs in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Jin said that drugs, cultural relics and pirated VCDs are the
major focus of the battle against smuggling.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
