<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebels Attack Army Detachment in East S.Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Three soldiers were killed and
nine others injured Tuesday night in Tricomalee, Eastern province
of Sri Lanka, when Tamil rebels fired mortars and launched an
attack on government troops, a military spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The rebels first fired at an army detachment before mounting a
major attack, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The troops retaliated with small arms and mortars, and
supported by arriving reinforcements, repulsed the attack. The
rebels suffered some casualties, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
MI-24 helicopter gunships of the Air force engaged the fleeing
rebels, and a search and clear operation was launched Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the government
for a separate state in the north and east of the country since
1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
