<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Province Exports 7,000 Tons of Maize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Nampula Province in northern
Mozambique has exported over 6,900 tons of maize to the
neighboring Malawi, given its bumper grain harvest in past few
years.
</P>
<P>
The province will also export 300 tons of maize to complete
its contracted goal of 7,200 tons.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed Tuesday by Selemane Girano, an official from
the Mozambique Institute of Cereals.
</P>
<P>
The province exported a total of 25,000 tons of maize
to Angola and Indonesia last year, Girano was quoted by
Noricias as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the current difficulty facing food
export is transport and granary, which had been destroyed in
the 16-year-long civil war.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that agricultural production in Nampula Province
has been on the increase in the recent three years. Last year,
the province produced over 810,000 tons of grain, a 3.4 percent
increase over the year 1996. 
</P>
