<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Vice-President in Ethiopia for ECA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Ghanian Vice-President John
Evans Attah Mills, arrived here Wednesday morning to attend the
40th anniversary celebrations of the United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa (ECA).
</P>
<P>
The vice-president will attend an international conference
with the theme of "African Women and Economic Development:
Investing in Our Future", which is convened to coincide with the
40th anniversary of the founding of the ECA.
</P>
<P>
The Ghanaian vice-president was welcomed here at the Bole
International Airport by Ethiopian Minister of Information and
Culture Wolde-Micheal Chemo and others.
</P>
<P>
ECA was established on April 29, 1958 with only eight African
member states, including three in the sub-Saharan region. It is
now composed of 53 member states, all of them independent states
of Africa. 
</P>
