<HEADLINE> Tang, Albright Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Since the end of last year, the two countries have gradually
put into practice the common understandings reached by the leaders
of the two countries in Washington by expanding and strengthening
the exchanges and cooperation in wide range of sectors, Tang added.
</P>
<P>
At the invitation of President Jiang Zemin, President Clinton
will pay a visit to China by the end of June, Tang said, adding
that this is another important event in the Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
