<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangxi Leads China in Sugar Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, one of the poorest areas in China, has emerged
as the country's major sugar producer with an annual output of 2.2
million tons.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent issue of the China Economic Herald
Tribune, the region has led the nation in sugar output for five
consecutive years and produces about a third of the nation's
total output.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is currently home to 109 sugar refining companies,
with the industry's total output value accounting for nine percent
of the region's total industrial output value. The sugar industry
also accounts for 10 percent of the region's annual fiscal income.
</P>
<P>
The skyrocketing growth of the region's sugar industry has
helped some 4.5 million people shake off poverty over the past 10
years, according to the paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
