<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee Name List for Macao SAR Passes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The name list of members of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR) was passed this afternoon by China's top legislature.
</P>
<P>
The second session of the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee approved the list, which includes 100
members. Forty of the names are from the inland areas of China,
and the other 60 from Macao.
</P>
<P>
The Preparatory Committee will be established in May with its
office in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen will be the director of the
Preparatory Committee, and the vice-directors will be Xie Fei, Ma
Man Kei, Liao Hui, Wang Qiren, Wang Yingfan, Ho Hau Wah, N.G. Fok,
Susana Chou and Stanley Ho.
</P>
<P>
Chen Ziying, vice-director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council, will serve as secretary-general of
the Preparatory Committee. Vice secretaries-general include Li
Shuilin, Xie Houhe, and Tina Ting Yee Ho. 
</P>
