<HEADLINE> Kiriyenko Appointed Executive of Belarus-Russia Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Russia's newly-elected Prime
Minister Sergei Kiriyenko Wednesday was formally approved by
Belarussian President Alexander Lukashenko to act as Chairman of
the Executive Committee of the Belarus-Russia Union (BRU).
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko, who is here for the one-day Customs Union summit of
the Commonwealth of Independent States, Wednesday handed over to
Kiriyenko the text of the decision that he made during the talks
with Russian President Boris Yeltsin in Kremlin on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The president pointed out that all problems between the two
countries must be tackled promptly in the interests of the two
states.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko, whose nomination of premiership was confirmed by the
State Duma, the lower house of Russia's parliament, on April 17
after three rounds of voting, expressed confidence that the BRU
will "undoubtedly continue to develop."
</P>
<P>
He also called for more strict implementation of the accords
signed between Russia and Belarus. "Good friendship is always
based on good economic relations," he added. 
</P>
