<HEADLINE> Four Investors Bid for Uganda Telecom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Four foreign investors have been
pre-qualified to bid for 51 percent shares in Uganda Telecom
Limited (UTL), the New Vision paper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The four bidders are Telecom Malaysia Berhad, Telecom South
Africa and two consortiums, with the first two bidding for the
full 51 percent shares on offer.
</P>
<P>
Portugal Telecom International, Aga Khan Fund for Economic
Development, and Alta Telecom International form a consortium. Of
the shares on sale, they want to buy 50, 40 and 10 percents
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Another consortium of Worldtel and Detecon is pre-qualified to
bid for 70 and 30 percent of the shares.
</P>
<P>
"With the recent issuance of a second national operator's
licence to the Mobile Telephone Networks Consortium, the
privatization of the UTL marks the final stage of the
government's telecommunications reform strategy," said Anne
Mugisha Bwomezi, the spokesperson of the Privatization Unit.
</P>
<P>
She added that the government is committed to a speedy
implementation of the UTL and the sale process is expected to be
completed by the end of July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
