<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Officials in Shanxi Province Urged to Reduce Bureaucracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The government of north China's
Shanxi Province has launched a months-long campaign urging local
officials at various levels to reduce bureaucracy.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, farmers in some areas in Shanxi
distilled and sold counterfeit low-quality spirits, which killed
more than 30 people and poisoned over a hundred others.
</P>
<P>
Some officials related were given serious warnings or
removed from their posts.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has since announced a decision that
local departments should review local bureaucratic practices
between April and July in order to curtail cases involving
dereliction of duty.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi Governor Hu Fuguo said that Shanxi has
a large number of hardworking and pioneering officials, but also
noted that a number of bureaucrats fail to exhibit
concerns for the well-being of the masses.
</P>
<P>
Those engaged in excessive bureaucracy, no matter how their
position, should be punished according to the law, said Hu.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
