<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Zoo Puts Newborns on Exhibit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Visitors to the Beijing Zoo can
now view over 100 young animals, recently born at the zoo or
introduced from other countries.
</P>
<P>
The new arrivals, mostly protected species, include giant
pandas, brown bears, golden monkeys and chimpanzees.
</P>
<P>
The youngster are somewhat shy of humans and tend to stay close
to their mothers.
</P>
<P>
The zoo, the largest in China, houses over 6,000 animals from
600 species. The zoo recorded some 1,500 births of more than 100
species in 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
