<HEADLINE> Enterprises in Qidong City Linked to Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 enterprises in Qidong
city, east China's Jiangsu Province, have been linked to the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
New Internest users include local state-owned and township-run
enterprises, as well as foreign-funded and private ones.
</P>
<P>
The Qidong Posts and Telecommunications Bureau invested three
million yuan in September 1997 to provide the Internet access to
local enterprises. The users now can timely exchange information
vis the global network and send E-mail rather than fax messages.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises can also use the Internet to publicise recent
progress and follow changes on the international market. The
Internet is more efficient and less costly, according to the
manager of a local foreign-funded enterprise.  
</P>
