<HEADLINE> IOC Supports Changes in Ice Dance Judging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee (IOC) announced that it supports calls for changes in
the judging system of ice dancing but will not drop the sport from
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
"We will be in contact with the ISU (International Skating
Union) to discuss the future of the judging," said Gilbert Felli,
sports director of the IOC.
</P>
<P>
Canadian vice president of IOC Dick Pound called for ice
dancing to be dropped until it cleaned up it judging at the IOC
executive board meeting.
</P>
<P>
But Felli said, "We trust this sport, there is no reason to do
that." 
</P>
