<HEADLINE> Chinese FM on Wei Jingsheng, Wang Dan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said today that if Wei Jingsheng and Wang Dan wanted to
come back to China, they must go through certain legal procedures.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark in answer to a question raised by the
press here after signing an agreement between the Chinese and US
governments on the establishment of the direct secure telephone
link.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that both Wei and Wang have violated China's laws and
they are criminals. They both went to the US on bail for medical
treatment at their own requests with approval by the Chinese
judicial department in accordance with relevent Chinese laws.
</P>
<P>
If they wanted to come back, they must also go through
relevant legal procedures, Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister said that China is quickening the
pace of introducing a legal system and promoting democracy, and is
making efforts to govern the country according to law. The bail of
Wei and Wang complies with this principle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
