<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Zambia to Accelerate Talks on Bilateral Treaties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Zambia have agreed to
accelerate their talks on several treaties on long-term bilateral
cooperation, local press reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The treaties include a framework agreement for economic, trade,
cultural, scientific and technological cooperation, an agreement
to avoid double taxation and an agreement to promote and protect
investment.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam and his Zambian
counterpart Eli Walubita, who arrived in Hanoi Tuesday for a
two-day official visit, discussed the matter later in the day.
</P>
<P>
Cam, also Vietnam's deputy prime minister, said that the two
nations should devise more measures to promote trade and economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Keli Walubita said Zambia intends to develop stronger ties with
Vietnam, particularly in agriculture and trade. 
</P>
