<HEADLINE> China, US Signs Agreement on Direct Telephone Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 29 (Xinhua) -- A direct telephone line between
the Chinese and the United States governments have been officially
facilitated as of today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and visiting US Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright have just signed the Agreement to the
effect in Diaoyutai, the State Guesthouse.
</P>
<P>
The Agreement Between the Government of the People's Republic of
China and the Government of the United States of America on the
Establishment of the Direct Secure Telephone Link, was signed in
line with the provisions described in the Sino-US Joint
Statement last October when Chinese President Jiang Zemin visited
the United States.
</P>
<P>
The Joint Statement states that the two countries ~agree
to a Washington-Beijing presidential communications link to
facilitate direct contact."
</P>
<P>
Albright arrived in the Chinese capital at 11:15 am for a
three-day visit at the invitation of her Chinese counterpart Tang
Jiaxuan.
</P>
<P>
Tan and Albright are scheduled to meet with Chinese and
US press people before holding talks on bilateral relations and
regional and international issues of common concern.  
</P>
</TEXT>
