<HEADLINE> Air Macao Carries Over Two Million Passengers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Air Macao transported more than two
million passengers by Tuesday night, a press release from the
company said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The air company has seen a fast-growing business since the
Macao International Airport was inaugurated in November 1995. It
received its millionth passenger in May last year.
</P>
<P>
Air Macao reported a net profit of 79 million patacas (about
10 million U.S. dollars) in 1997, the first profitable year since
its establishment.
</P>
<P>
It now has a fleet of six airbuses. The 7th aircraft will
arrive in Macao on Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The carrier is now operating air routes to Beijing, Shanghai,
Xiamen, Qingdao, Wuhan, Fuzhou, Nanjing in China's interior areas
and Taipei, Kaohsiung in Taiwan. It also has regular flights to
Manila and Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Its 8th destination in China's inland -- Chongqing, will be
inaugurated on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After that, the weekly flights of the carrier will add up to
117, destined to 12 cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
