<HEADLINE> Tragic Shipwreck Exposes Illegal Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A shipwreck in the Lake of
Nicaragua in which 16 Ecuadorians died on Monday has exposed an
underground network which illegally took South Americans to the
United States through Central America and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
The shipwreck happened when the network was taking 17
Ecuadorians from San Jose to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Only one Ecuadorian, Juan Macao Cardenas, aged 21, survived the
tragic accident.
</P>
<P>
The boat, overloaded with double of it's capacity sank Monday
night in the middle of storms and high waves.
</P>
<P>
The illegal workers had been charged six thousand U.S. dollars
to be taken from Ecuador to the United States. Half of this was
handed over at the beginning of the trip, and the rest was to be
settled when they reached their destiny.
</P>
<P>
But their dreams of going to the U.S. were obliterated in
Nicaragua, leaving only their corpses on the shores of the
Nicaraguan lake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
