<HEADLINE> Thai Students Get Chance to Work in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. authorities will from
Monday allow Thai and other Asian students suffering from the
financial crisis to apply for jobs in the United States, according
to the Thai Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS) is
passing a regulation in the federal registrar to let students from
Thailand, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines and South Korea
work in the country, Thai Foreign Ministry Spokesman Kobsak
Chutikul was quoted Wednesday by the Bangkok Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
The students seeking jobs will have to inform advisers at
respective educational institutions. Then application forms will
have to be submitted to the INS head office, which will issue work
permits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
