<HEADLINE> 13 Panama Workers Killed When Elevator Cable Breaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, April 27 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen construction workers
were killed and one seriously injured Tuesday when the elevator
they were on plunged from the 20th floor of a 25 storey building.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the victims crashed against the payment when the
cables supporting the elevator broke. Eight of them died at the
site and five died on their way to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian construction industry has registered 50 tragic
accidents, in which more than 100 people died, over the last five
years.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Labour Union of Construction Workers of
Panama expressed that the construct industry has become the
most dangerous one in the country. 
