<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Biggest Solely Overseas-Backed Venture Starts Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 29 (Xinhua) -- The Minebea Precision
Electromechanical Corporation (Shanghai), a solely Japan-funded
company involving a total investment of 348 million US dollars,
has started operation in Xicen Town, in Shanghai's suburban Qingpu
County.
</P>
<P>
It is the largest solely overseas-financed business in
Shanghai, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The company has been in trial production for four years, with a
first-phase investment of 4.9 million US dollars, the sources
said, adding that the investment has been steadily increasing.
</P>
<P>
It now operates a bearings production center, with a
present monthly output of 10 million units, and an electric fan
motor production center which is capable of producing 3.5 million
units a month.
</P>
<P>
The company pays great attention to environmental
protection. It has constructed facilities to treat waste water and
a pollution-free trash furnace at a cost of six million US
dollars, established an environmental protection fund and planted
trees on 40 percent of the company's factory land.
</P>
<P>
Minebea Japan, the parent company of Shanghai Minebea, is a
professional maker of miniature and small bearings used in
computers and high-tech electromechanical products, and has 40
production bases and 70 marketing centers located in 18 countries,
occupying 65 percent of the world market for miniature and small
bearings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
