<HEADLINE> Tajikistan Landslides Toll Rises to 42 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The death toll for the landslides
in the mountainous area in southern Tajikistan rose to 42
Tuesday. 50 to 60 other people are missing.
</P>
<P>
A Monday report by the Interfax news agency said the disaster
had killed 19 people, injured 16 others and left more than 400
homeless.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures put the economic losses resulting from the
landslides at 65 million U.S. dollars. The landslides on Sunday
were caused by torrential rain and hailstorms, and heavy rains are
estimated to continue until the end of May.
</P>
<P>
Tajik President Emomali Sharipovich Rakhmonov sent condolences
to the relatives of victims Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Tajik army and militia are doing rescue operation at the
site, and have been joined by personnel from the United Nations
Development Program and the International Red Cross, which have
sent material including food, medicines and clothes to the
disaster area.
</P>
<P>
Tajikistan has not experienced a natural disaster on such scale
for 30 years. 
</P>
