<HEADLINE> Venezuela Suggests Reduction of Oil Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela suggested on Tuesday
other oil producing nations to reduce their production by 500,000
barrels a day to prop up the falling international oil price.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela, Mexico and Saudi Arabia signed an agreement in March
to reduce their production by 200,000 and 300,000 barrels per day
respectively to cope with the outbreak of an oil pricing crisis.
</P>
<P>
The production cut once stabilized the market, but 500,000
barrels per day is the amount required by the market, said
Minister of Energy and Mines of Venezuela Erwin Arrieta.
</P>
<P>
He said Venezuela will have to decrease it's production by 10
percent to reach that amount.
</P>
<P>
New cut may be agreed upon by the countries before the
conference of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
(OPEC) in June, the minister said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
