<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Weightlifters Make Clean Sweep </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Ivanov led a Bulgarian sweep on
the first day of the European weightlifting championships in
Riesa, Germany, on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, Olympic champion from 1992, won gold in the men's
56-kilogram category. Compatriots Donka Mintscheva and Isabella
Dragneva took the titles in the women's 48-kg and 53-kg divisions,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 48-kg class, Bulgaria won both gold and silver
with Mintscheva beating Siika Tomparova into second place.
</P>
<P>
Mintscheva dominated the field in both snatch and clean and
jerk by managing 70 kg and 92.5 kg respectively for a total lift
of 162.5 kg.
</P>
<P>
Tomparova lifted a total 155 kg while Hungarian Aniko Ajkai
took bronze with 152.5 kg.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov outclassed the opposition with a winning total lift of
282.5 kg compared to only 260 kg for Turkey's Sedat Artuc and
Bulgarian Naiden Russev, second and third, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dragneva won with a total lift of 182.5 kg. Dagmar Danekova of
Slovakia and Anna Stombou of Greece came second and third with
177.5 kg and 157.5 kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
