<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan to Pour Funds Into Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Province, China's
second-biggest island, is to invest a total of 3.6 billion yuan in
an environmental protection program, named the "Green Project",
over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The province will also give priority to foreign investment for
the project, according to a provincial official.
</P>
<P>
The project will focus on the treatment of urban sewage and
rubbish, the harnessing of major rivers and the protection of
precious plants and animals, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, Hainan is expected to launch 16
sewage-treatment projects and six garbage-disposal projects, and
set up 12 nature reserves. 
</P>
</TEXT>
