<HEADLINE> Myanmar, India to Cooperate in Civilian Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 29 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar and India have reached an
agreement here on cooperation of the two countries following a
two-day Myanmar-India Civilian Officials National-Level Meeting.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed on Tuesday between Myanmar Deputy
Minister of Home Affairs Brigadier-General Thura Myint Maung and
visiting Indian Home Secretary B P Singh, official the New Light
of Myanmar newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report did not disclose further details of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Indian secretary, who led a five-member delegation, arrived
here last weekend for the meeting. 
</P>
