<HEADLINE> Hungary Police to Enhance Protection of Foreign Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hungarian police has decided
to enhance its protection of foreign tourists affected by the
worsening public security.
</P>
<P>
Police chief Forgacs Laszlo declared on Tuesday that hundreds
of special policemen will be placed in the capital and other major
tourist areas during the peak tourism period from July 1 to
September 15.
</P>
<P>
Recently cases of explosions and murders have been on the rise
in Budapest and other cities. Diplomatic missions from the
European countries here have asked Hungary to adopt measures to
improve public security as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Also, the Hungarian police will strengthen the security work in
areas surrounding the frontier inspection stations, especially those
bordering Australia, Romania and Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
