<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornado Hits Coast of Buenos Aires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 28 (Xinhua) -- A tornado destroyed homes
and cut power supplies when it tore through the Atlantic coast of
Buenos Aires on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The tornado, with winds of more than 100 kilometers per hour,
lasted almost 30 minutes in the area between "Mar de la Plata" and
"Villa Gessell", about 200 kilometers south of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The strong winds ripped away the ceilings of several dwellings,
uprooted trees, interrupted the traffic on many routes and caused
a blackout in the area, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A strong rain and wind storm also hit the area Tuesday night,
flooding many houses in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine government has sent medicines, food, clothing and
shelters to the victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
