<DOCNO> XIE19980429.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Firms in Guangdong Break into World Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 29 (Xinhua) -- More and more private firms in
Guangdong Province are entering the world market by exporting
products and setting up overseas subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong, adjacent to Hong Kong, is a national pioneer of the
private economy. In 1997, the province had 123,000 private
businesses, ranking first among all provinces in the country.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 960 private firms in the
province have exported products each with annual foreign exchange
earnings topping 180.7 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than 300 private firms have been involved in
joint ventures and cooperative ventures with overseas partners;
more than 1,000 of them are engaged in export-oriented processing
and compensation trade; and more than 50 have set up overseas
subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
Among them is the Tianjian Company set up by three farmers of
Siqian Township, Xinhui County with a pool of 1,000 yuan (120.48
U.S. dollars) a dozen years ago. Their furniture firm has not only
exported their products, but also set up two overseas
subsidiaries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
