<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Loan For Moldova's Real Estate Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank decided Tuesday
to grant Moldova a 35-year loan of 19.5 million U.S. dollars to
boost the country's real estate sector.
</P>
<P>
A release issued by the World Bank said the money would mainly
be used to set up a system of real estate registration, the
Bucharest-based Mediafax said.
</P>
<P>
Poor information and ambiguity in ownership had severely
hampered the development of Moldova's real estate business and its
national economy, the release said.
</P>
<P>
So far, the World Bank has provided 277.9 million U.S. dollars
in loans to facilitate 11 projects in Moldova. 
</P>
</TEXT>
