<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Backs Baltic Nations' EU Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro said Tuesday that Italy backs Lithuania, Latvia and
Estonia in their bid to join the European Union and NATO.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro made the remarks when meeting his Latvian counterpart
Guntis Ulmanis.
</P>
<P>
In a speech in Riga, Scalfaro said Italy was "at your side in
your legitimate aspiration to attain full integration" into the
EU, but NATO entry is more problematic because of Russia's
security concerns.
</P>
<P>
According to Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini, the
expansion of NATO to include the Baltic states must be pursued "in
harmony with Russia in order to achieve an overall strengthening
of pan-European stability."
</P>
<P>
Italy is also concerned over Latvia's large Russian minority,
which accounts for almost a quarter of the country's population,
Italian officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
