</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji pledged that China's policy of
developing transcentury friendship and relations of cooperation
with the Kyrgyz Republic will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark yesterday during a meeting yesterday with
visiting Kyrgyz President Askar Akyevich Akayev.
</P>
<P>
-- Jim Dae-Jung, president of the Republic of Korea, said
China's development will be important to peace and stability on
the Korean peninsula throughout the new century, as well as the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Kim, who made the remarks while meeting visiting Chinese
Vice-President Hu Jintao yesterday, said Hu's tour will enhance
relations between ROK and China.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China welcomed yesterday the European Union's (EU) decision
to remove China from the list of non-market economies in its
anti-dumping policy.
</P>
<P>
The action represents a big step forward by the EU in modifying
its anti-dumping policy towards China and will help Sino-European
economic and trade relations, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu
Bangzao said at a routine news briefing in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- The worst effects of the financial turmoil are now over and,
after a period adjustment, Hong Kong will surely regain its
vigor, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Chief
Executive Tung Chee-hwa said. 
