<HEADLINE> Korda Advances in Czech Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Five out of eight seeded players
fell at the Czech Open men's tournament on Tuesday, but local
favourite and top seed Petr Korda advanced into the second round.
</P>
<P>
The victims included French fourth seed Cedric Pioline, the
beaten finalist in the Monto Carlo Open on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
World number two Korda overwhelmed compatriot Petr Kralert, a
world 354th-ranked wild card entry, 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Czech Radomir Vasek eliminated third seed Karol Kucera of
neighbouring Slovakia 6-2, 1-6, 6-2 while Italy's Renzo Furlan
dispatched Pioline 0-6, 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
In other matches involving seeded players, Czech Michal Tabara
beat fifth seed Richard Fromberg 7-6, 2-6, 7-5; Spaniard Jacobo
Diaz dispatched number eight Marcelo Fillipini of Uruguay 6-2,
6-4, and Andrei Chesnokov of Russia ousted number seven Jeff
Tarango of the United States 7-6, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
