<HEADLINE> Capriati Beats Labat in Hamburg Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Jennifer Capriati, gold medalist in
the 1992 Barcelona Olympic Games, produced an upset victory over
Florencia Labat on the opening day of Hamburg Open here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Capriati, who has not cause any ripple after her Olympic
triumph, was playing just her fourth event of the year.
</P>
<P>
The world 227th-ranked Capriati humbled the world number 34th
Labat 6-2, 6-4 in 67 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sixth seed Sabine Appelmans of Belgium was tumbled out by
Russia's Elena Likhovtseva.
</P>
<P>
Appelmans was beaten 6-0, 3-6, 6-3, and admitted she had found
difficulty in transferring to clay from her recent Federation Cup
matches on hard courts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
