<HEADLINE> Ronaldo Gets Two-game Suspension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Inter Milan star Ronaldo was given a
two-game suspension Tuesday by the Italian League for criticizing
the referee who worked his club's controversial loss at Juventus
of Turin.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan coach Luigi Simoni and Brazilian midfielder Ze
Elias are both out for the rest of the league season with
three-game suspensions while Chile's Ivan Zamorano will sit out
two matches.
</P>
<P>
The disciplinary committee's rulings came two days after some
questionable refereeing in a match that likely decided the league
champion. Juve's 1-0 win gave it a four-point standings lead over
No. 2 Inter with three games left.
</P>
<P>
In the second half of the Sunday's match, referee Piero
Ceccarini failed to whistle a clear foul on Ronaldo and then
awarded a penalty to Juve's Alessandro Del Piero at the other
end. Ceccarini then turned to eject Simoni, who ran onto the
field to argue.
</P>
<P>
Ze Elias was expelled from the game with 11 minutes left for
throwing an elbow at the head of Juventus midfielder Didier
Deschamps. 
</P>
