<HEADLINE> UN Appeal to Urgent Humanitarian Aid to Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The Office for the
Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs on Tuesday appealed to the
international community to provide urgent humanitarian aid to
Southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations is deeply concerned by the humanitarian
situation in Southern Sudan, especially in the Bahr el Ghazal
region where an estimated 350,000 people are in need of urgent
humanitarian assistance, and in the area of Bentiu in Unity state,
where an estimated 22,000 people are in need of assistance, and
malnutrition rates are reported to be as high as 31 percent.
</P>
<P>
Operation Lifeline Sudan has been attempting to deliver food
and relief supplies to the affected population in those areas.
</P>
<P>
The Office requested donors to respond urgently and generously
to the 1998 United Nations consolidated appeal which is seeking
109.3 million U.S. dollars to meet the food and non-food needs of
war and drought-affected Sudanese. 
</P>
</TEXT>
