<HEADLINE> Wall Street Still Cautious </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street were
mostly higher Tuesday, but blue-chip issues retreated after an early
rally, as investors were still cautious about the actions of the
Federal Reserve.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average fell 18.68 points to 8,898.96,
after attempting an early rally.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 3-to-2 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 677.75 million shares as
against 685.01 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock measures also pulled back from the morning's
highs, but several lost steam. The Nasdaq composite
index posted the biggest gain after suffering the heaviest damage
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index, which plunged 49 points on Monday,
rose 10.08 to 1,830.39.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list slipped 0.65 to 1,085.89,
but the NYSE composite index rose 0.51 to 563.56.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 3.83 to 472.33,
and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 4.03 to
733.03.
</P>
<P>
The Dow lost 147 points on Monday amid suggestions that the
Federal Reserve is considering an increase in interest rates to
slow the economy and keep inflation under control.
</P>
<P>
The bond market, jolted by Monday's developments, struggled
again today, with the yield on the 30-year Treasury pushing
farther above 6 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
