<HEADLINE> S. Korean President to Visit U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim
Dae-jung is expected to pay an official state visit to the United
States in early June, a U.S official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kim Dae-jung will discuss with U.S. leaders issues such as
South Korea's progress in meeting terms of an International
Monetary Fund financial rescue and the four-party talks on the
Korean Peninsula peace process, the official said.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no shortage of things to talks about," he said.
</P>
<P>
The final dates for Kim's visit have not been set, but it might
precede a trip by President Bill Clinto to China planned for late
June, the official said. 
</P>
