<HEADLINE> Moldovan President on CIS Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The discussions concerning the
present and the future of the CIS, raised in the last summit, will
be continued in Moscow, the President of the Republic of Moldova
Petre Luchinsky Tuesday said in Kishinev on his departure for the
summit of CIS in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
Petre Luchinsky emphasized the necessity of creating
possibilities for cooperation on the basis of the new principles.
</P>
<P>
The President said that a regime of free trade, existing in the
world should expand in the CIS, adding "all the member states are
interested in it". He stressed that this problem should be
thoroughly discussed at the inter-state CIS forum on issues
dedicated to the reforming of this structure.
</P>
<P>
According to the Moldovan news agency INTERLIK, a meeting of
the heads of the CIS member countries will open on Wednesday in
Moscow. The summit's agenda includes a wide range of issues,
concerning the strategy of the Community development.
</P>
<P>
A considerable attention will be paid at the summit to the
problems of military cooperation. The Republic of Moldova does not
participate in the framework of the CIS.  
</P>
</TEXT>
