<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Backs Telecommunications Reform in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 28 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved here
Tuesday a 30 million U.S. dollar loan for the Telecommunications
Reform and Privatization Support Project in Romania.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to assist Romania in reforming the
telecommunications sector, including privatization of existing
public sector telecommunications facilities, providing the
necessary infrastructure to enable the General Inspectorate of
Communications (GIC) to maximize the productive use of the radio
frequency spectrum, as well as improving frequency assignment
criteria for further expansion of wireless communications
services.
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the project is some 44 million dollars. Apart
from the World Bank loan, the GIC will provide 12.2 million
dollars. The Romanian government and the European Union will share
the remaining cost for the project.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the World Bank commitments to Romania total 2.6
billion dollars for 19 projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
